title: 820-3437 No PP3V3_S5
message: Board came in liquid damaged primarily in the clock chip area. Had 8.58 on PPBUS, 3.42 on 3v42 and green light. Had 0 volts on PPVRTC_G3H. Replaced C1902, C1922, and C1910 because they looked bad as well as the clock chip. Now I have 3.42 volts on PPVRTC_G3H, 5 volts on PP5V_S5, but zero volts on PP3V3_S5. The only bad probe point I found was the one left of R2042 but it seems to have continuity to its corresponding spots. On the TPS, SMC_PM_G2_EN is 3.42 volts, P3V3S5_EN_R is 3.3 volts. What am I missing or where do I go from here?

title: 820-3437 No PP3V3_S5
message: All the basics are there so it is either a short on 3V3_S5, bad TPS51980 or a corroded trace/resistor in that area.

title: 820-3437 No PP3V3_S5
message: Ok will check those and get back to you

title: 820-3437 No PP3V3_S5
message: 3.9 kilohms and rising despite 0 volts. Did not see really much of any corroded traces or resistors besides the ones in the clock area and everything connects. Will replace TPS tomorrow and check back

title: 820-3437 No PP3V3_S5
message: Ok so replaced TPS same problem. Went back to clock chip area pulled chip noticed PCH_CLK32K _RTCX1 pad was burned so ran jumper to corroded test point now have continuity and replaced clock chip again. Same problem no 3V3_S5. I'm really stumped on this at this point nothing else looks corroded or broken. Also PM_SLP_S5_L is missing checked all test points near BIOS all connect and all of the probe points look pristine. The only other probe points on the board that look anywhere near discolored are one by the SMC for SMC isense which I don't think is related at all and then the probe points below the CPU. Is this a time waster at this point?

title: 820-3437 No PP3V3_S5
message: Oh, and I still have 3v3 S5 enable.

message:

message: I have no idea. TPS is getting enable signals so it should work. As I said VREF2 should be 2V and you have 1. Bad TPS, bad cap, resistor, trace it is somewhere around the TPS.
